Very friendly place and staff. An interesting and innovative exhibition. I recommend!

It's not very big and when I went there I found the Expo very mediocre. Unfortunately in contemporary art we often border on fraud because real artists are rare. At the Tignous center in any case, apart from two works, we were left wanting more. Not the best way to honor the memory of this iconoclastic cartoonist, victim of the attack on Charlie Hebdo.
Two lovely exhibitions during the holidays, this week again not to be missed: Suspended Lives. Thank you for the welcome to the Tignous center team.

One Sunday afternoon, not knowing what to do with the children, we arrived at the Tignous center... And we were not disappointed! A very warm welcome, a beautiful exhibition and above all a very nice creative workshop. Upstairs, we were welcomed by a young artist who presented to my children various workshops (related to the marmoe festival) of sculpture on wood, stone, clay, cardboard, paper... The children loved her workshops and create beautiful works of art! Thanks to the whole team for the welcome
Beautiful photo exhibition and installations on the theme of teenage bedrooms from around the world. Surprising!

Very beautiful exhibition space with an interesting program, particularly for the works of Anahita Bathaie, among others for the Lointain Proche exhibition.

The place surprises rue de Paris which had accustomed us to other businesses...but here it is a private hotel whose mezzanine is currently devoted to the "tignus for ever" Expo; well stocked and pleasant we have a great time there.
